d the normal workflow.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering guidance on actions**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how they might ignore guidance if there’s no action specified. The prompt seems to expect JSON only, without a schema to enforce actions or guidance. I’m leaning toward no action if there's strictly no requested setup, but I should include the risks involved. Also, I want to revisit this idea of “before meaningful coverage is reachable”—is meaningful coverage achievable with normal generated tests for Janino? That’s something to consider!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying setup properties**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the test setup. It looks like the environment or system properties aren't really needed after all. However, there's \\\"other test-code setup guidance\\\" that involves package relocation. I should clarify that while guidance is important, package relocation isn't just setup — it's part of the code content. I can set the action to \\\"no_action\\\" and specify that \\\"No environment/system property/test setup is required.\\\" That seems straightforward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"Janino 3.1.0 does not need extra setup beyond the normal test scaffold: its required commons-compiler artifact is a transitive dependency, and normal documented usage is in-process compiler/evaluator APIs without Docker or environment/system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. The observed javac failure is a source-compatibility issue: org.codehaus.janino.util.iterator.Iterables is no longer present in janino 3.1.0; tests should avoid that old internal package or use the relocated org.codehaus.commons.compiler.util.iterator.Iterables if iterator utilities are intentionally covered.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The optional org.apache.ant:ant dependency is only needed if tests deliberately exercise Janino Ant integration; do not add it for normal compiler/evaluator coverage.\",\n    \"Janino dynamically compiles and loads classes, so native-image limitations still need validation through the existing Gradle/native-image tasks.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06f9635bdf965d82016a4262ebb13481969a1a8fd4780ff96c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1103, "output": 1776, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25407, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782735570317, "responseId": "resp_06f9635bdf965d82016a4262d4444c81969409171e3c0d3091"}, "toolResults": []}
